.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::AppData \- NIP\-78 Arbitrary Custom App Data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::AppData;
\&
\&    # Store app\-specific data
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::AppData\->to_event(
\&        pubkey  => $pubkey,
\&        d_tag   => \*(Aqcom.example.myapp/settings\*(Aq,
\&        content => \*(Aq{"theme":"dark","fontSize":14}\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse app data from an event
\&    my $ad = Net::Nostr::AppData\->from_event($event);
\&    say $ad\->d_tag;    # com.example.myapp/settings
\&    say $ad\->content;  # {"theme":"dark","fontSize":14}
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::AppData\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-78 (Arbitrary Custom App Data). Provides
remoteStorage <https://remotestorage.io/>\-like capabilities for custom
applications that do not care about interoperability.
.PP
Kind 30078 is an addressable event. The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag contains a reference to
the app name and context (or any other arbitrary string). The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR
and other tags can be anything or in any format.
.PP
Use cases include:
.IP \(bu 4
User personal settings on Nostr clients
.IP \(bu 4
Dynamic parameters propagated from client developers to users
.IP \(bu 4
Private data for apps that use Nostr relays as a personal database
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 4
\&    my $ad = Net::Nostr::AppData\->new(
\&        d_tag   => \*(Aqmyapp\-settings\*(Aq,
\&        content => \*(Aq{"theme":"dark"}\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::AppData\*(C'\fR object. All fields are optional.
\&\f(CW\*(C`extra_tags\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR. Croaks on unknown arguments.
Typically returned by "from_event".
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS to_event
.IX Subsection "to_event"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::AppData\->to_event(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        d_tag      => \*(Aqcom.example.myapp/settings\*(Aq,
\&        content    => \*(Aq{"theme":"dark","fontSize":14}\*(Aq,
\&        extra_tags => [[\*(Aqversion\*(Aq, \*(Aq2\*(Aq]],
\&        created_at => time(),
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30078 addressable Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`d_tag\*(C'\fR is
required and becomes the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR defaults to empty string.
\&\f(CW\*(C`extra_tags\*(C'\fR, if provided, are appended after the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. Any
remaining arguments are passed through to "new" in Net::Nostr::Event.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ad = Net::Nostr::AppData\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 30078 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::AppData\*(C'\fR object. Returns
\&\f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event kind is not 30078.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $ad = Net::Nostr::AppData\->from_event($event);
\&    say $ad\->d_tag;
\&    say $ad\->content;
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::AppData\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-78 event. Checks that the kind is 30078 and a \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
is present. Croaks if the kind is wrong or the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag is missing.
Returns 1 on success.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::AppData\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid: $@" if $@;
.Ve
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS d_tag
.IX Subsection "d_tag"
The application identifier string from the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. Can be any
arbitrary string referencing the app name and context.
.SS content
.IX Subsection "content"
The event content. Can be any format (JSON, plain text, etc.).
.SS extra_tags
.IX Subsection "extra_tags"
Arrayref of additional tags beyond the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. Can be anything
in any format.
